      <h4 class="green-section-heading">Sustainable food systems to platform career paths</h4>
      <p>Food systems intersect all three dimensions of sustainability --environmental, social and economic.  By underscoring the common threads between sustainability and food systems for its core guiding principles, UYS provides a pipeline that other related programs can build and showcase their specialty upon. Accordingly, UYS outcomes are community-centered, narrated by members, mobilizing social norms to build a community its members identify with and to stay with.</p>
      <p>Urban Youths for Sustainability (UYS) is a youth core job training program for urban youths for 14-24 years old. Its focus on growing own food and environmental stewardship directly engages community youths to tackle the persistent food insecurity and environmental pollutions in the urban communities, along with job insecurity.</p>
      <h4 class="green-section-heading">Collaboration to pipeline for collective changes</h4>
